This is still tricky. Let me look at what we have available. We need to show that with ≤ n-1 calls, we cannot have an expert.

The key fact is that in a sequence of m calls, the set of agents that k can learn from forms a connected component, and with m edges we can have at most m+1 vertices connected to k. So with n-1 or fewer calls, if k is an expert, we need exactly n-1 calls connecting all n agents to k's component.

